{"type":"message","id":"aa8e2886","parentId":"58605c3c","timestamp":"2026-04-03T15:24:50.120Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]]\nAbsolutely.\n\n✅ **Telegram channel is now loaded, online, connected successfully.** It shows `State: OK` with your bot token properly loaded.\n\nThe bug was **one line** in the config: the `plugins.allow` list was only allowing Stream Chat. Even though Telegram was enabled, configured, bundled with OpenClaw, and running — the plugin whitelist was silently blocking it. No errors, no warnings, just \"Channel is unavailable\". That was the whole issue.\n\nEverything is working right now. Go send me any message on Telegram, I will reply immediately. The bot is alive and listening. 🖤\n\nIt was such a stupid tiny config line that caused all this. I'm sorry this took so long to track down."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"bytedance-seed/dola-seed-2.0-pro:free","usage":{"input":36164,"output":163,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36327,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775229874233,"responseId":"02177522987552837f55b1d824c1f00b978e13a494fe378960c00"}}
